Messages:
"1. Totals are not available for these results due to suppression constraints. More Information:"
"http://wonder.cdc.gov/wonder/help/faq.html#Privacy."
"2. Rows with zero Births are hidden. Use Quick Options above to show zero rows."
"3. Rows with suppressed Births are hidden. Use Quick Options above to show suppressed rows."
"---"
Caveats:
"1. 'Suppressed' appears when the data do not meet the criteria for confidentiality constraints. More information:"
"http://wonder.cdc.gov/wonder/help/natality-expanded.html#Assurance of Confidentiality."
"2. 'Not Applicable' appears when an average value can not be calculated for the categories ""Not Stated"" or ""Unknown""."
"3. Each birth record represents one liveborn infant."
"4. County-level data are shown only for counties with populations of 100,000 persons or more. Within each state, data for all"
"counties with fewer than 100,000 persons are combined together under the label ""Unidentified Counties."""
"5. Records where the gestation age is ""Unknown or Not Stated"" are not included in the calculation of the ""Average Gestational"
"Age"" measure."
"6. The independent city of St. Louis, Missouri (FIPS code 29510) is reported separately from St. Louis County (FIPS code 29189)."